                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d110">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">422.11G93/1026: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hartman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-07T15:00:00-05:14">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 7, 1919, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received May 8, 8.05 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Representative of Foreign Bondholders in Guayaquil has requested me to bring
                    pressure to bear on Ecuadorean Government to resume payments daily deposits
                    which ceased in February. Have advised him Legation will act only on
                    instructions from the Department. Report by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
